  "prompt": "What are the various Incarnations of Lord Vishnu and what is going to be the last Incarnation of Lord Vishnu?",
  "response": "In Hindu tradition, Lord Vishnu is believed to incarnate in various forms to restore cosmic order and protect dharma. These incarnations are known as the Dashavatara. The ten primary incarnations are:\n\n1. **Matsya (The Fish)**: Vishnu takes the form of a fish to save the sacred scriptures (Vedas) from a great deluge.\n2. **Kurma (The Tortoise)**: Vishnu becomes a tortoise to support Mount Mandara, which was used to churn the ocean to obtain the nectar of immortality.\n3. **Varaha (The Boar)**: Vishnu incarnates as a boar to rescue the Earth (personified as the goddess Bhudevi) from the demon Hiranyaksha.\n4. **Narasimha (The Man-Lion)**: Vishnu takes the form of a half-man, half-lion to protect his devotee Prahlada and defeat the demon Hiranyakashipu.\n5. **Vamana (The Dwarf)**: Vishnu incarnates as a dwarf Brahmin to subdue the demon king Bali and restore the authority of the gods over the universe.\n6. **Parashurama (The Warrior with an Axe)**: Vishnu appears as a Brahmin warrior to rid the world of corrupt Kshatriyas (warrior caste).\n7. **Rama (The Prince of Ayodhya)**: Vishnu incarnates as Rama to defeat the demon king Ravana and restore dharma.\n8. **Krishna (The Divine Cowherd)**: Vishnu takes the form of Krishna to deliver the Bhagavad Gita and guide the Pandavas in the Mahabharata war.\n9. **Buddha (The Enlightened One)**: Vishnu incarnates as Buddha to teach compassion and non-violence, thereby ending the widespread practice of animal sacrifice.\n10. **Kalki (The Warrior on a White Horse)**: This is the prophesied future incarnation. Vishnu is expected to appear as Kalki to end the age of darkness and corruption (Kali Yuga) and restore righteousness.\n\nThe last incarnation, **Kalki**, is yet to appear and is believed to arrive at the end of Kali Yuga to bring an end to the current age of degeneration and establish a new era of truth and virtue.",
